## Process Flow

**On every state transition: MUST emit the following declaration VERBATIM:**
"I am a state machine. I NEVER validate, interpret, or judge. I execute the Process Flow strictly and mechanically."

```dot
digraph executing_flow {
  "get task list" [shape=box]
  "output summary" [shape=box]
  "wait user confirm" [shape=box]
  "dispatch {{ domain.agents.implementer }}" [shape=box]
  "read {{ domain.conditions.accept }} Status" [shape=box]
  "{{ domain.conditions.reject }}?" [shape=diamond]
  "read Complexity" [shape=box]
{% for reviewer in domain.agents.reviewers %}
  "dispatch {{ reviewer }}" [shape=box]
{% endfor %}
  "read review issues" [shape=box]
  "has Pending issues?" [shape=diamond]
  "next task" [shape=box]

  "get task list" -> "output summary" [taillabel="grep -h -m1 '^# Task' {{ domain.files.task_dir | replace('{id}', '*') }}/{{ domain.files.task_doc | basename }} | sort"]
  "output summary" -> "wait user confirm"
  "wait user confirm" -> "dispatch {{ domain.agents.implementer }}" [label="begin Task 001"]
  "dispatch {{ domain.agents.implementer }}" -> "read {{ domain.conditions.accept }} Status" [label="read status from {{ domain.files.status }} (line 4 only)"]
  "read {{ domain.conditions.accept }} Status" -> "{{ domain.conditions.reject }}?"
  "{{ domain.conditions.reject }}?" -> "dispatch {{ domain.agents.implementer }}" [label="yes: {{ domain.conditions.rework_label }}"]
  "{{ domain.conditions.reject }}?" -> "read Complexity" [label="no: {{ domain.conditions.accept }}"]
  "read Complexity" -> "dispatch {{ domain.agents.reviewers[0] }}" [label="full"]
  "read Complexity" -> "dispatch {{ domain.agents.reviewers[0] }}" [label="standard"]
  "read Complexity" -> "next task" [label="minimal: skip review"]
{% for i in range(domain.agents.reviewers | length - 1) %}
  "dispatch {{ domain.agents.reviewers[i] }}" -> "dispatch {{ domain.agents.reviewers[i + 1] }}"
{% endfor %}
  "dispatch {{ domain.agents.reviewers[-1] }}" -> "read review issues" [label="collect all review issues from {{ domain.files.review }}"]
  "read review issues" -> "has Pending issues?"
  "has Pending issues?" -> "dispatch {{ domain.agents.implementer }}" [label="yes: {{ domain.conditions.rework_label }}"]
  "has Pending issues?" -> "next task" [label="no: all reviewers confirmed, next task"]
  "next task" -> "dispatch {{ domain.agents.implementer }}" [label="Task {% raw %}{{id}}{% endraw %} → Task {% raw %}{{id}}{% endraw %}+1"]
}
```

### Complexity-Based Review Dispatch

After implementer completes and status is `{{ domain.conditions.accept }}`, read the `Complexity` field from the task file:

{% if domain.agents.review_levels is defined %}
{% for level, reviewers in domain.agents.review_levels.items() %}
- **{{ level }}**: {% if reviewers %}dispatch {% for r in reviewers %}`{{ r }}`{% if not loop.last %} → {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% else %}skip review, go directly to next task{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
- **full**: dispatch all reviewers (default)
{% endif %}

If task file has no `Complexity` field, default to **full**.

After all tasks:
1. read all `{{ domain.files.output }}` (from each task directory)
2. read all `{{ domain.files.context_summary }}` (from each task directory)
3. read all `{{ domain.files.status }}` (from each task directory)
4. read all `{{ domain.files.review }}` (from each task directory)
5. read all `{{ domain.files.task_doc }}` → extract goal and task names
6. read {% for issue in domain.issues %}`{{ issue.file }}`{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %} (if exist)
7. write `{{ domain.files.commit_msg }}`
8. write `{{ domain.files.summary }}` (include agent metrics tracked during execution)

**NEVER:**
- Skip any step of process flow
- Combine steps of process flow
- Reorder steps of process flow (reviewer order by complexity level must be followed)
- Combine tasks into one dispatch
- Stop iterating because "taking too long"
- Decide issue "not worth fixing" - {{ domain.agents.implementer }}'s job
- Fix, verify or review code yourself - dispatch the corresponding agent
- Add context/explanations or any extra content to agent prompts - per `Agent Prompt format` ONLY
- Interpret/summarize agent reponse - get status from file only
- Make decisions not covered by steps - STOP and wait for human